sentences: Fierro was born in Mexico in 1942 and grew up in El Paso, Texas.
He became a member of the rock band the Sir Douglas Quintet in 1968.
In 1971, Fierro played saxophone and flute on Hooteroll?, an instrumental, free-form album by guitarist Jerry Garcia and keyboard player Howard Wales.
He appeared on the Dead's album Wake of the Flood in 1973 and toured with them that year.
In 1984, Fierro joined the Bay Area Jam Band Zero alongside founding members Steve Kimock, Bobby Vega, John Cipollina, and Greg Anton.
He was diagnosed with cancer and died in 2008.

sentences: Martin Fierro (January 18, 1942 – March 13, 2008) was a saxophonist who played with the Sir Douglas Quintet, Quicksilver Messenger Service, Jerry Garcia, and Zero.

In later years he played with the jam bands the String Cheese Incident and the Dark Star Orchestra.
